The <a href="complex%20number">complex</a> absolute value function is continuous everywhere but <a href="complex%20differentiable">complex differentiable</a> "nowhere" because it violates the <a href="Cauchy%E2%80%93Riemann%20equations">Cauchy–Riemann equations</a>.

The second derivative of  with respect to  is zero everywhere except zero, where it does not exist. As a <a href="generalised%20function">generalised function</a>, the second derivative may be taken as two times the <a href="Dirac%20delta%20function">Dirac delta function</a>.

