The absolute value is closely related to the idea of distance. As noted above, the absolute value of a real or complex number is the <a href="distance">distance</a> from that number to the origin, along the real number line, for real numbers, or in the complex plane, for complex numbers, and more generally, the absolute value of the difference of two real or complex numbers is the distance between them.

